Sharon Osbourne is replacing Brandy as a judge on the U.S. reality TV series
America's Got Talent.
The 54-year-old wife/manager of rock singer Ozzy Osbourne will debut May 29,
when the televised talent contest commences its second season.
She will join returning judges David Hasselhoff and British media figure Piers
Morgan. Talk show host Jerry Springer will host the contest, which carries a $1
million prize.
